			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Is epic a gimme?<a name="3397"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 21 03 6:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been lurking here for a few weeks, and my young Bard is only level 35.  I've played a bit towards the end game with a monk (level 56 - pre PoP).
<br />

<br />
Listening to the conversations here it seems that getting the bard epic is just part of the natural progression.  It seems that it will come naturally somewhere in the early 50's.
<br />

<br />
On my server, there is a Trak rotation, with only about 10 guilds on it.  For the most part, a character can't even get into those guilds until they achieve level 55 or more.  
<br />

<br />
I am on the outside of those 10 or so guilds, and the guild I am in is a tiny group of friends.  I don't understand how a bard like me would even see Trak, let alone be part of a raid to kill him. Phinny's probably a lot easier, but getting people there seems to be impossible. There are enough pickup raids that I could see eventually getting my scales from Naggy and Vox.
<br />

<br />
Is that the answer?  Abandon my guild when I turn 55, join a top ten guild, wait 3 months before I loot anything, and hope they eventually grace me with an epic somewhere down the line?  Is there another way?
<br />

<br />
Keldridge
<br />
Level 35 Bard
<br />
Emarr </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
