			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is epic a gimme?<a name="3398"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 21 03 7:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm not the perfect person to answer this but I have my own thoughts about yours and my dilemma alike.
<br />

<br />
First off, in no way would I consider the bard epic to be a gimme or a natural progression.  IMHO the bard epic is one of the most difficult to acquire in the game, just on the sheer fact that you need to kill at minimum 3, likely 4 dragons to get what you need (if you think that you must kill Trak twice).  If you want more confirmation, click on people's names and see if they have their epic received box checked. Of the folks that populate the 50+ forum, I doubt you will find that more thatn 20% of them have their epics.  We all want it, but it is harder than hades to get.
<br />

<br />
Secondly, I am level 53, am 2/3 through Page 25 and have barely touched the next phase.  I am in an incredible guild that is not currently able to take out the dragons I need for my epic.  I am not willing to leave my guild for the sake of my epic.  If we never grow and mature (level), I will remain epicless, though we are growing and leveling quite nicely.  
<br />

<br />
The two options I see form myself I see for you as well.  They are:
<br />

<br />
1) Make friends, preferbably those in guilds that would be willing to assist you with the more epic parts of your epic.  
<br />

<br />
2) I imagine your server, like mine, has a server-wide board, where you could schedule and open raid on the mobs in question. Where also you could make as a condition of joining, agreeing that you will loot the item in question.  A fallback position would be to roll on it, but that would suck for lack of a better word.
<br />

<br />
If you like your friends, I don't see the rationale for leaving for the sake of an item, even if that item is your epic.  Again, this is my opinion, you are welcome to yours.  I prefer to make my guild better such that we can get our epics. Of course the very nature of our guild is to help each other do what we cannot do alone, so I am biased.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian Barelytone</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
