				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is epic a gimme?<a name="3451"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 23 03 8:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>No item is worth leaving a guild of friends for.  So you will have a nice new shiny pointy object?  What about the comrads you abandoned to get it?  
<br />

<br />
I am in a similar situation - guild of friends.  I am 4 steps from the epic (Phinny, Eldrig, Red Dragon and Trak).  I will complete all the steps except Trak.  Then I will stop.  Always in the back of my mind is hope, but deep down I know it isnt going to happen.  Does it bother me?  Honestly, maybe a smidgeon. Will I go to an uber guild to help me take down trak?  Nope.  The people I play with are more important than the items in the game.
<br />

<br />
However, since that little flame of hope always lives, one thing I have done and will continue to do, is to befriend other guilds, join their outting, and make a name for myself.  That way in oh say, 2 years (*LOL*), if I can arrange a trak raid, I will have support from many on Bristlebane.
<br />

<br />
Dont bust a gut about the epic.  It does not define you.  Only you can do that.</span></td>
