				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is epic a gimme?<a name="3593"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 03 10:21 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is part of the social interaction of the game.  Make lots of friends.  In the &quot;end game&quot; how many people you know makes all the difference.  Leaving a group of friends to play this end game is not worth any item to me.  If anyones intention is to get items and levels and become the most powerful &lt;insert class here&gt; then you are playing the wrong game.  The bard epic is so amazingly useful but it is not a requirement to the progression of a bard.  Play your game, do your epic pieces one by one if it is your plan t do your epic at all.  When the time comes you will have the support you need from FRIENDS when it is needed.  Naturally as you make higher levels you meet higher level people.  Show courtesy and generousity to everyone and i promise you will never have much trouble putting together raid parties when the time comes.</span></td>
