				<td colspan="2"><span>This thread makes me curious.
<br />

<br />
I'm currently level 44, and I only need the eldrig guts and the fear whip.
<br />

<br />
I did page 24 (both parts) totally on my own.
<br />

<br />
I killed Blackwing for the onyx drake guts with a druid friend, he died in 30 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Nezzie, a 61 Ranger offered to kill for me. He brought a 65 Mage friend, and the epic pet tanked. Nez died in all of 20 seconds.
<br />

<br />
I bought both the red and white scale from bazaar (7k each, which I farmed myself.)
<br />

<br />
And as I've posted in another thread, I have a friend willing to MQ the phinny spine for me.
<br />

<br />
After I get the whip and the chromo guts, and a few more levels, my guild is perfectly capable of taking down Trak. I'm hardly in an 'uber' guild, however they are one of the higher-end guilds on Saryrn, doing HoT and the like. Hardly a raid guild, it is a rather close-knit bunch, and I'm a very proud member. They're just waiting for me to get 46+ to do fear, and I've been caming SF for some week now with no sightings. Still too small to kill there on my own, but I keep hoping folk killing there for Cleric shards will spawn Eld.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
But, it just makes me wonder why people think the Bard epic is one of the hardest? If I've come this far, by level 44, just with a few friends, none of them guildies, how hard is it for a 55+ to do the same? h*ll, a 55+ Bard could probably kill Eldrig and Nez themselves with enough effort put in.
<br />

<br />
I'm not a twink, this is my first character. I'm still wearing the same gear I've had for some 20 odd levels, all of which I've worked my butt off farming money to buy. But I've come this far just because I'm persistant. Do I *need* my epic? No. The SSS doesn't make a Bard, as handy as it is. However it *is* something I want. It's one of my goals in the game, and once I set my mind on something, I do my d*mn best to achieve it.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Is this wrong of me? Am I incredibly lucky? Or am I aggorant in assuming pretty much anyone can get folk to help them kill the larger monsters involved? Obviously, Trak does require a good raid force, but everything up to that can be done without being in a large guild.
<br />

<br />
I dunno about other servers, but there's a couple guilds I've come across that are happy to do final epic raids for folk, even if they're not in the guild. You've done everything but Trak? Sure, they'd go help you with UDB and clone-trak, just for the fun of it. Is this uncommon elsewhere?
<br />

<br />
Okay, I dunno, maybe I'm just small and clueless. I'm also extremely tired and shouldn't be trying to sound corherent at 3am, so I'll end this post now.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
