				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm not sure I'd call you lucky, hard work is not luck, though there are some things out of your control that COULD be considered lucky.
<br />

<br />
For one, you bought the scales for 7k each. That's 14k that you worked very hard for. Multiply that effort by 4 to come close to what that would cost me on my server.  My guild COULD do the red scales, though as I've been told it's doubtful that we could take Gore so why bother with the red yet.  There's no way we could take Trak either.  I haven't even bothered to ask strongly for help other than on Nez which took a partial group.
<br />

<br />
As for a 55 bard soloing Nez or Eldrig, I'm 55 and I wouldn't dream of soloing either. Yeah it's possible to fear kite them, but with resists you would have 2 twist fear to keep it up, charm or mez the adds you got, and tank down a mob that would likely take 10+ min to melee solo.  In fact, just FINDING Eldrig is a royal pain, at least until 56 (one yellow to go yay!) when you can just gate all the mobs to their spawn point where your group is camped, then hot-foot it to zone to lose aggro while they keep him busy and get back to kill and loot.
<br />

<br />
If the guilds on your server are as helpful as they sound then you are lucky IMHO. My server isn't mean per se, but it is very doubtful they would mobilize a raid force to go kill a dragon for another guild's bard.  That being said, when the time comes, I will have the three guilds in our alliance, and likely a hodgepodge of folks I've helped or my friends have helped.
<br />

<br />
As for the bard epic being hard, what other class has to kill a MINIMUM of 3 dragons to get?  None.  I've helped with the cleric epic in every major battle and though the Chardok Nobles was a major raid, the triggered Ragefire was a pushover.  I haven't fought our Ragefire (doesn't seem to be the same as I've never seen scales drop from the cleric triggered one), but I'd expect it's harder, kind of like the spawned Trak, vs the triggered Trak.  Could be wrong here but you get my point.
<br />

<br />
Lastly, the druid epic. As a 53 druid that is 3 corrupteds and Fay from completion (no real hurry to complete the leaf blower here), the corrupteds are fairly cake (duo'd most of them with a 55 necro friend) just longish boring camps. I say longish becuase the most I've waited was 3 hours for one and I've heard of folks sitting for over 10 hours in Seb waiting for the UDB to pop. That and I've found that Fay is the weakest of the oldworld dragons and can be taken with a good two group mini-raid.  I have not done one lately due to timing problems, but my guild has thrown together 4 or so impromptu Fay raids where less than a dozen folks showed up.  That doesn't sound like any of our dragons unless those dozen people are two perfectly balanced 65 groups that know how each other play.
<br />

<br />
In the end, GRATS bud, you are farther along than I am because I'm not willing to farm 60K for my scales.  You make several good points and I hope you get yours soon. Just remeber that some of the turnins require you to be 51+. Don't want to see all your time and effort go poof.
<br />

<br />
Sorry for the long post.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
