				<td colspan="2"><span>I play on Innoruuk where my Druid gained her epic in a way not familiar to most.  We have a group of people called Team Epic, www.teamepic.org.  This group was started by a number of people who were in smaller guilds that, on their own, had no chance of taking on the larger epic mobs.
<br />
The way this works is you get help based on how much help you give to others.  Certain larger events are planned, and other smaller events are on a pickup group basis.  This has allowed us to get many people their epics that would have had to otherwise purchase MQ's or just plain not get their epic due to other circumstances.
<br />

<br />
I would encourage all servers to adopt such an institution so that friends do not get put out due to the lack of forces for larger mobs.  Pretty soon you'll also find that you've made a large number of friends in the game which you may not have known otherwise.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
