				<td colspan="2"><span>Just my 2 cents on the bard epic.  Even though I do not have it yet (being only lvl 43) I plan on getting it.  I feel that the bard's epic is a lot easier than other epics.  Now, most likely I will get a little flame/slam for that comment, but my main is a warrior with his epic, and the warrior epic I feel is a lot harder to get.  On my server (and probably most other servers) the green scale is the hang-up for the warrior's epic.  You have to be very lucky to get a shot at Sev (or you have to have a guild that does VP, which is slim to none).  And then you have to get a group of people willing to spend 2 days minimum in PoA clearing  islands to get to the spiroc lord.  Most of the time, people don't have that kind of time, or they will work from there on to get the elemental binder for the mage epic.
<br />

<br />
Now, with that said, I can throw out a suggestion on how to get trak done (he is not that hard).  Keep an eye out for the undead bard.  You see him on track, get you guild and some buds to help out with it, you could even do a /ooc open epic raid in PoT.  I've seen it done before, and more likely than not, there will be people willing to help out with an epic fight.  I've done it before where people needed tanks for epic fights.  I'm sure there are people on your server that would be willing to help out also.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
