				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is epic a gimme?<a name="11799"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 4 03 1:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is not a post on the epic but on Guilds.  I belonged to one of the oldest guilds on Bristlebane which finally faded away because we could not compete for the higher end raid encounters.   Even though everyone enjoyed playing together we could not keep the higher level players happy and after PoP the guild folded - we merged with another guild.
<br />

<br />
My feeling, at least for Bristlebane, is that this is enivitable for medium sized guilds.  Eventually you will get to where you cannot go any further and you have to choose to be happy where you are or move on.  Most people choose to move on.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
